message.content:
cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.GR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper discusses the construction of a low-cost home-made tracking system for a toy quadcopter to make it autonomous. This falls under the domain of robotics.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The tracking system is based on web-cams and involves pose estimation of the quadcopter. This involves computer vision techniques such as feature detection and matching, and hence falls under this category.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the use of an "Internet of Things" mini-board to control the quadcopter and make it autonomous. This falls under the domain of systems and control.
- cs.GR (Graphics): The paper discusses the use of markers on the quadcopter for tracking. This involves computer graphics techniques such as marker design and placement.
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper involves the use of web-cams for tracking and the construction of a low-cost tracking system. This falls under the domain of multimedia systems.
